==English==
===Noun===
''a'' '''[[blue]] [[moon]]'''

# (''rare'') The [[moon]] tinted towards [[blue]] as it appears in the sky, caused by dust or smoke in the atmosphere.

===Etymology===
Earliest known use is a 1528 pamphlet titled ''Rede Me and Be Not Wrothe''

===Noun===
''a'' '''blue moon'''

# (''obsolete'') The third [[full moon]] in a quarter that contains four rather than the usual three full moons.

===Etymology===
Mistake in Sky & Telescope magazine in 1946, retracted nearly 60 years later.

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
''a'' '''blue moon'''
# The [[second]] of two [[full moon]]s that occur in the same [[month]].
#(''by extension'') A long time.

